caption: Oh, my, a small shack with a phenomenal version of bao s made me rethink the bao movie all over again. The owners were strict on COVID guidelines, almost suggested that I do a take out but yet the food was beyond awesome. Tried most bao's and did not find a bad one at all. Give them a try. You won't be disappointed
My favorite spot in the Loop! I recommend the bao especially the chicken, pork and shrimp!
Got to try the duck gumbo!
OMG the food is amazing flavors is everything

LOVED the food. Got the paella and bao tacos (bacos) and they were both delicious. I’ve never been anywhere that served anything like it. On top of that, staff was very good about following cautious COVID preventing procedures and were very friendly!
The food was awesome!  Service was great!  Very helpful staff if you have never been there and need food suggestions.
Amazing lunch spot! Sandwiches and rice bowls are filling and delicious. Great for take out or delivery. Fast, friendly service!
Delicious carry-out during social isolation! Lots of nice vegetarian options, too. Spicy blend of flavors.

I had tried crispy vegetables in appetizer and drunken noodles, fried rice and green curry for the dinner main course. All vegetarian options. Crispy vegetables, Drunken noodles, and green curry were amazing. I quite liked them. Fried rice was little too dry and rice doesn't come along with curries. Overall a good, inexpensive meal.
Tasty but can be pretty expensive. Very crowded around 12pm but getts better 30 minutes later.
Food was awesome!  Interesting selections!
Best lunch in the loop
The place is superb and broad, the meals was delicious and the prices were very reasonable. quick, effective service and very affable staff. I highly recommend this place.
Good food, i want to try the duck gumbo! Just don't get the shrimp rice bowl. Its 14$ and all you get is literally shrimp with white rice.
Got food poisoning from the Paella and girlfriend has gotten the runs from this place on a separate occasion. This location need to work on keeping their food clean.
Extraordinary environment and super friendly service. The food was crisp and yummy. Will surely recommend this restaurant to friends and family. Reasonable prices and large meals. Great work.
Very tasty!
Even better then the food was the awsome staff!

About a year later this place has become my favorite in the city. Banchan has improved significantly over time. Great selection of meats, especially if you prefer non marinated options. Weekend lunch special is excellent.
Had a good experience in this spot with my kid. The food came quick and the service is just excellent. Prices are convenient.
Love this place... everyone there is amazing.
It was interesting. My mouth was a little confused, but the flavors were very good. The spring roll was overcooked, though.
Great food
Latin asian fusion at its best

Do not judge the book by its cover. Hidden gem in the south loop of Chicago. Large portions with incredible taste. I had the Paella and the chorizo egg roll as a side. Highly recommend both. I can’t wait to go back  to try one of the sandwiches.

A great meal. The loaded fries are a huge portion, even the ‘small’ size. Bacos were great and the meat inside was well seasoned. Closed out with the doughnut dessert that might have been the best thing I had. Here just around the corner for a training and very glad this was in the search results for ‘restaurant’ in my immediate vicinity. Worth seeking out. Bring friends so you can order, split and share. Apparently also Guy Fieri approved!

We ordered catering from Saucy Porka and it was AMAZING! The delivery staff were great to work with and set everything up to ensure the food looked great and would taste even better when our event attendees were ready for lunch. Make sure to try the Nutella donuts!
I eat here a lot since I work close by. I got to say their service is always excellent and they keep the place neat consistently. Prices are affordable and they serve big portions.
Good food!!! Funkey Monkey fries are awesome.
Shrimp Back, fried plantain, shrimp po boy
Average food

They are the only Filipino fusion cuisine in the loop (that I know of). Everything is delicious, including their awesome pork ramen. They also are known for their delectable Baco’s (think tacos meets wow bao). This place feels familial and if you want to try something new that’s not ordinary, I would highly recommend this saucy fast casual! Yum.
Staff is really nice and welcoming. Food is not as authentic and flavorful as expected from other reviews.
This is one of my current faves, the egg rolls are so flavorful and delicious, the shrimp and corn baos are super good, definitely give this one a try if you like asian latin fusion
Great asian fusion cuisine. Definitely worth 5 stars

Service was amazing. We brought our 1 year old daughter with us and they were just great with providing extra napkins and utensils and stuff like that for her without asking. We decided to get an extra bao for her and they didn't charge us. We're not in Chicago often but wouldn't hesitate to come back again to support them. Oh and on top of great service, excellent food.
So amazing

The picadillo and the chorizo  egg rolls are delicious!! We had to order extras because we wanted more. The paella is also really good, but wouldn’t order it again. Portions are generous. Friendly staff!
Great food, fast service.
Chorizo egg rolls are super good. I also liked the sweet potato fries and aioli sauce. For a place that’s pretty popular the prices aren’t bad. Next time I have to try the bowl which looked amazing.
Best Lo Mein noodles I have ever had, Most friendly staff and recommended entrees. My Husband had  ydon soup and Japanese rice beer.
Tried several of the appetizers, all were flavourful and also had the wasabi noodles.  Overall really good dishes and the service was over the top.
It was absolutely amazing! Natalie made several suggestions on what to get and try and they were all amazing! I ordered the Chorizo Egg Roll, Da Funky Monkey Fries, a pork Bacos and duck Bacos.
Interesting concept of mixing Asian and Latin food, however execution is not the best. The Bacos (baos and tacos) were not as amazing as they sound.
A little confused, but ok.
Great little fusion stop.  Friendly staff.  They helped me through the menu.  Had the Duck Gumbo which was delicious. Seems that Guy Fieri dropped by too and liked the food.

Love the food here and the people who work here are friendly and helpful. The menu has some great variety of choices without being overwhelming. Everything I've had there tasted great. The only reason I don't give this a higher rating is because The restaurant lacks any real ambiance. It's cramped. It's crowded (because the food's so good and the people are so great). I'd love to see them move into a larger nicer space.
Loved the food and fusions. Great people.

This was a real let-down.  Having been away from SoCal for the past six years, I perk up any time I discover a new Korean joint here in what, if we're to be honest, is essentially the midwest.  Last week, I was working downtown at Sears, and happened across this place with those enticing words "Banh Mi" posted up outside. So I of course went in.  Having ordered the standard pork Banh Mi, what I received was nothing at all what I've become accustomed to in the Koreatowns of LA and NYC, to say nothing of Seoul itself. The baguette was of good quality, but it was utterly devoid of the fresh, crisp vegetables, saucy Kimchi, and savory dry-roasted pork, containing instead a uniform slurry of greasy, roughly homogenous filling which I could best describe as a mixture of cheap canned kimchi and oily pork trimmings, with no discernible texture.  I'm sorry if you're the owner and you're reading this. Maybe I just showed up on an off day. But this was really, without question, the worst Banh Mi sandwich I have ever eaten. No crunch. No diversity of flavor.  No discernible evidence at all of carrot, cucumber, daikon, or anything else besides a sickly meat slurry bathed in weak chili paste.
Pretty good food, especially the baos. Had doors open on a hot day though.
I love their banh mi, chorizo rolls and rice bowls. Haven’t tried the bacos ... yet
Will have to come back and try the rest. Had all the Bao Buns. They were okay.
Deeeeeeelicious. Fast and friendly service!
Insanely good food.

We visited the downtown location and the place is far from expectations, no directions for simple stuff as how to place an order, once the order was placed no one told us that to get your drinks you need to get them out of the fridge yourself, out order was incomplete and when brought to the attention of the lady at the register  she mentioned that since we pallid cash there was no way to find our if in fact we asked for the missing part if the order.
Saucy, good tasting
Try the Monkey fries. So filling.
Great fusion place, cashier was very nice when taking my order. The place was also clean
Awesome
The food is phenomenal 🤯🤤 the servers are so helpful and friendly 👍will be my favorite band mi place for the rest of my life!
Good
Consistent and lot of flavours! Can't stress enough you have to try their sandwiches.
Good food that you aren't going to see anywhere else.
Great food. Usually quite busy for lunch but they move through the line quickly.
Great service.  Interesting menu
Mondays made marvelous with Saucy's Breakfast banh mi and Vietnamese coffee.

I've been wanting to try this place for a long time now, but have never been able to make it since their business hours are M-F 8am-3pm. I finally was around the area at the right time was excited to try! Parking was a hassle and expensive.  I ordered a beef, pork, duck, and chicken baco. They were all good, but pork and duck was my favorite. Kinda pricey though for the size. It's nice to try, but probably wouldn't go out of my way to come back.
(Translated by Google) Very good food  (Original) Muy buena comida
I had the Puerto Rican bowl with pork and a fried egg. The pork was delicious, the rice was bland, and I wish the egg was over easy. It was between ok and good overall.
Good food Fun place Check out the new location in Hyde Park too
The duck bao is a must.

I cannot rave about this place enough! Excellent lunch break spot for working in the loop. Every menu item is delicious and the staff are extremely friendly and polite. Even though it’s a quick bite kind of place, the staff will still go above and beyond to wait on you and refill your drink, clear your table, etc. The lady working the cash register is upbeat and gives honest recommendations. You can really tell they care about this establishment, and heart and soul are put into the food too. I try something new every time but always order the chorizo egg rolls. Out of this world! There’s a reason I keep coming back - if you haven’t been you NEED to go!
Bao here is really good so was the beef egg roll
Great customer service awsome food
Very Tasty!

Unique dishes, fresh and delicious, spicy but not overwhelming. Attentive staff come by to refill water and pick up plates. But no bathroom--even for customers? I give em 5 stars anyway but you might not if you stick around there drinking water too long.  Don't be fooled by Google -- there is no longer a location on Financial Place, only on Franklin Street about 2 blocks northwest.  UPDATE 2019/03/15 When checking out, the cash register suggests tips that include 11.5% sales tax in the total, which is an annoying way to cheat customers. I took off 1 star.
Their loaded fries are great and their pork bacos are unique
Small portions, but tastes good
I bought Ban Mi. New strange taste. Everyone should try once.
Absolutely great lunch joint.... Check out the menu!!!
For anyone looking for something new and different instead of more of the same, this place is perfect.  I was not only impressed by the quality but the creativity they put into their food.
Fantastic for mid week lunch .. Try the Picadillo egg roll
A but pricey, but good food.
Amazing bacos. Get the pork or shrimp
Friendly service, fast turnaround and DELICIOUS food!
Always awesome. I dream of their Pozole. Chorizo egg rolls were tasty, but salty for me, great sauce with them. Asian paella is different but quite nice. Bacos are all quite good.
I was barley acknowledged, and did not feel very welcomed. Food overpriced, and just ok.
Let me tell you what totally sold me on this idea: the beef barbacoa. Fabulous.
Good for lunch
Great food!
Kimchi nachos, barbacoa boas, this place is amazing.
It's a small place and unassuming, but the food is great and priced well for a quick lunch. Great if you are looking for something a little more unique
Very good Asian, Tex/Mex place for lunch.  Braised beef is my fav.
Not only is the food awesome here, but the entire staff is just so nice. Like cousins welcoming you home for a meal
Food was alright, and the staff was very friendly and kind
Such an amazing find. Loved the sweet potato fries, it tasted amazing

The food here is to die for, I had the egg rolls, lemonade, and a pork boa. I would recommend this to anyone in the financial district. The food is moderately priced I ate for under $10. Thank you for hosting us!

It was good place
Great food!  Love the Latin asian fusion.
Delicious and fast! Fusion at its best. Many vegetarian/vegan selections. Casual atmosphere.

I actually appreciated this diner, the food is outstanding, and also the restrooms were not smelly. It was a little chilly inside, so that was not the most enjoyable. The atmosphere is great. I will certainly consider returning once again if I have the chance. Me and also my friend got the toast and also we were not dissatisfied. My one recommendation is to maintain the cold exterior. Come again!

I've eaten here a few times now and enjoy everything I have tried. They are always fast, friendly and fiercely delicious! It's a great lunch option for unique fusion food in a sea of restaurant chains in the loop area.
Pretty good place. Bacos (esp. the carnitas) were good and the rice bowl was tasty as well. Friendly and quick service.

I was looking for a new spot for lunch, and this place appealed to me. I was greeted at the door by a very friendly staff. I placed my order for Asian paella. While it didn't taste bad, I was disappointed. I understand it was s fusion dish, but it  just seemed like rice, beef and some sausage. I didn't taste the paprika, nor any saffron. Whatever else you do to make it a fusion dish, it is not paella without those 2 ingredients. I also missed the peas. I'm going back to check out some other items on the menu.
Saucy Porka is one of the best Asian/Latin fusion places in Chicago.  The Paella bowl is simply delicious!!
I like the rice bowls but not the kimchi fries.
Friendly staff but food quality is horrendous.  Nothing to do with Asians dishes.  An aberration to Asians food.
Delicious!
Love the food. Prices are a bit high. A combo or meal option would be nice. But I keep going val because the food is really good. It is unique as well, being a fusion restaurant.
The food was really good. I got the Picadillo and thought it was delicious and filling. I look forward to going back and trying other things on the menu.
Delicious unexpected food combinations. Yum!
Baco's (tacos made with a bao bun) were delicious. The shrimp was my favorite followed by the barbacoa. The pork was a bit dry and not crispy enough.

This place can get a little cramped during lunch on weekdays, but what good restaurant in The Loop isn't? The line moves pretty fast. The food is consistently flavorful and the service is always friendly. This is a great place to grab something to go if you need to head back to your office.
Just went to the Hyde Park location.  Welcoming and polite staff - very helpful.  Enjoyed Tostones, The Saucy Porka, and some Bacos.  Can't wait to go back!
I love this place.. amazing food and the staff is wonderful
Very tasty!
work rush lunch, this fusion works, quick service
Delicious bacos and friendly service! The bacos had flavourful fillings and perfectly steamed bun. I'll definitely go again!
Don't let outside look of the building stop you because there is good food inside!

Wow. I can't believe this was the first time I'd been here.  They have bowls and so I ordered the beef with fried egg and garlic rice and a bottled coke.  Deeelicous!  It was made fresh and that made it all the more yummy.  I also ordered the fried chicken pieces to go with a couple of their dipping sauces.  Now, that was sooo good!  Can't wait to go back and try more Menu items.
Amazing tender meat and interesting flavor combinations. Must check this place out. Workers are really nice.Would be awesome if they made handmade salsas too.
Best lunch spot in the loop - you don't want to miss this one of a kind fusion lunch. Check out the Asian Pallela.
Cool concept.  Great Bacos
💛 Wonderful, friendly service + innovative fusion of flavors 💛
Loved the Cheesy Buddha

Great tasting Bacos, the Duck gumbo is great, I like Duck so it works for me, I get a small boal and a single Bacos for around $10.  Small place limited seating, get there early are plan on getting it to go. I take it to the courtyard of the building just to the west of it and sit outside.
Love the shrimp bacos! Try them!

I had a trio of Bacos and the chorizo eggrolls...oh my nom, nom, nom! The steamed buns were a wonderful addition to traditional carnitas and shrimp tacos...but, the surprise winner of my trio of Bacos was the curry chicken...a little piece of heaven right there! Quick and delicious lunch spot!
I was really intrigued by this place. The menu was different from every restaurant close by. Give it a try if you're near. You will love it!

Big things come in smaller packages.Don’t be fooled by the size of the tacos because they are jammed pack with flavor! The Piccadillo egg rolls were even better. Not sure what the name of the orange dipping sauce is but its sweet and tango and I poured it everything. Perfect lunch spot!
The baos are a great option for a small snack. They're too expensive to turn into a full meal. The chorizo egg rolls weren't anything special. It is completely full with chorizo meat and not fillers.
Yummy Baos. But a little pricy
Picadillo egg rolls and phozole are mighty tasty
Great food. Fresh and fast.
Love this place. Get the bacos! Steak Pork Duck Chicken etc. I also love the duck gumbo.
Affordable and delish lunch!
Horrible hours that are typical of the loop area. Food and atmosphere was amazing! Try the chorizo egg roles with Asian-fusion guacamole!!! Fast service and cool hipster ambience
Great suggestions for newbies. Solid flavor. Fast service. Gluten free options!!! This is my type of Chicago spot.
So incredibly good. Very busy at lunch time.
Amazing place in Downtown Chicago. Asian-Latin Real fusion!!!
Excellent lunch food, good value, excellent service
Great food with tons of flavor, large portions, great prices and fast and friendly staff.
Chorizo eggrolls are amazing!

Good small shop vibes with Latin music playing in the background. The decor reminds me of the architecture and art of the Pilsen neighborhood. Prices are reasonable for the area. Decent selection of food on menu. I was impressed by the nice and welcoming staff. I tryed the Cubana sandwich at first. The bread is soft and holds well. The pork and carnitas were cooked well and juicy. Looking forward to trying more.
Great food. Tacos were smaller than I expected
Inventive and super tasty
the pork carnitas and the thai chicken curry bacos were great!
Had a carnitas/cubana sandwich so flavorful good stuff 👍
The bacos are amazing!

Both the food and people are amazing. The food is a combination of Vietnamese and Cuban. Even though the food was a bit spicy, it gave the food more flavor. The food's size is reasonable for its price. I recommend the ropa vieja with egg on top.
Quick, tasty, affordable and friendly! Perfect spot to grab a bite.

Truly fusion ethnic foods as advertised. The food is made with unexpected combinations: ban mi with shredded pork and kimchee, or the deep fried sweet potato in french fry style and sprinkled with green onion. The place mostly serves the lunch crowd and is closed after 3 pm and on weekends.  There are only about 10 small tall tables with bar stools. After we ordered at the counter the food came within 5 minutes.

I really like the concept of this restaurant and their food is definitely good, but it is also over priced. I paid over $17 for a rice bowl which had some beef, kimchee, and a fried egg (was extra too) plus a fountain drink. It tasted pretty good but that price was hard to swallow. I might go back but there are so many other more reasonable restaurants.
Awesome food!
Boring, very simple and the price isn't as simple as the meal
Great, quick food. Inattentive, self involved wait and counter staff.
Great good. I usually get the bowls and you will not be disappointed. The chorizo egg roll is fantastic.
The taste is good.
Good service. Quality food. Loaded fries, kimchi fries 👌
Great place with fantastic food. Quick service.
Great fusion lunch spot with unique flavors at a reasonable price.
Tofu bacos were excellent. The bao is so soft and fluffy and the tofu is fried very crisp, in a sweet ginger sauce. It was a delicious vegan lunch option in the loop.

Banh mi is very good with the carnitas and whatever Asian sauce is on the sandwich. The Phozole is also good but I think I prefer Pho by itself and Pozole by itself. However I have no idea where to get good authentic Pho or Pozole in the loop. Definitely worth a try.
The Bahn mi sandwiches, “bacos,” and phozole are amazing. Never had a bad meal here.
Crowded, very small, food is good
Loved it!  The bahn-mi sandwich is excellent!
Shrimp rice was not great

Had my lunch at this place, the staff is super friendly and will throw in suggestions on what to get. For a place of its size, the menu is quite big. 5 Different types of banh mi (for those that know). Ordered a rice bowl and no regrets.
Incredibly tasty food to heal your soul + friendly faces and great service.
Great flavor, looking forward to trying more combinations in the future
Pricey, but good.
Bacos. 'Nuff said.
What a great change of pace. Fresh, fast and friendly. Thanks for the great meal!
Awesome pork bun taco hybrids. Their menu has something for everyone and the staff was super cool and attentive for a quick bite type of spot.
They have some great vegetarian options- cheese buddha is one of the best sandwiches in town! Fast, no frills counter and friendly staff!
This place is absolutely amazing. Their fusion choices are both delicious and quite satiating. Love everything on their menu, must try for everyone especially if you love flavors

We were in Chicago for our first day of vacation, looking for a hole-in-the-wall place with interesting food. Delicious little pork tacos and big rice bowls plus a very welcoming, clean, and refreshing atmosphere. Great experience.
Absolutely amazing food. Love the ambience and great service.
Nice lunch spot. Very crowded at noon, but half an hour later returns to normal.
My go to place for lunch when I visit Chicago. They have bao tacos called bacos which are delicious. Tried pork, shrimp, chicken and duck. Yumm!
This is the first place I stopped on a visit to Chicago. It may have been may favorite meal. Great food and friendly service.
Great food and flavors! Price for amount of food is on par with similar restaurants. Fast friendly service.
Duck gumbo and boas are amazing good
The food is okay but a little pricy. About average for the area. The wait sometimes good, sometimes annoying. Friendly staff.
Super friendly staff. Excellent food. Fast service. I ordered the shrimp Baku which was ok and the rice bowl / black been / tofu which was amazing.

not really sure why it has this many positive reviews. the place itself is cute and the wait staff is quick and efficient. I tried the toru baco and i didnt like it as much, I will get the pork if I go back. And the vietnamese coffee. I tried the beef and that was a lot better, with good flavors and pineapple on the top. I got the curly fries as well but didnt like the curry that it came with, the fries were good, the scallions add a nice touch to them. Not really out of this world, but nice addition to the meal. I think i might come back for breakfast some day, those options sound better than the ones I had for lunch
Delicious. Had lunch ordered in from here. Everything tasted great.
Great Asian fusion food!
A regular spot for lunch. Unique food via Asian Cuban food. Love it!!!
Omg... The pork ramen is just awe!

I can't believe this place gets so many positive reviews. I ordered a braised rib rice bowl. The meat was dry and the dish had no flavor.. To top it off, the rather large girl that took my order was rude. I am never going back. Don't waste your money here.
Game.  Changer.  Chorizo spring rolls are a revelation. Fusion in the best way.
Great food

Based on all the 5 reviews i read, i was expected something outstanding. What a deception. I'm trying to look for new places for lunch and every day i try a new place. And so far, this is the worst lunch experience i have had. I took the asian paella. It was dry and the packaging was very cheap. Staff was unfriendly. So when i read reviews that this place is the best with best staff ever encountered, well...i doubt that all 5-star reviews are true.  So far, my best lunch places for take away have been  brightwok and roti. At these places, the value offered to customers is incomparable. I also liked Fire fin.
This place is amazing. Monkey fries are great as is the duck gumbo.
My panang curry sandwich was decent, but the blueberry lemonade was awesome
I love the execution of this concept Asian/Latin fusion. Everything was delicious and arrived quickly. Lunch options aren't served until 10am . Loved the curry fries and Vietnamese coffee

One of My favorite lunch spots! I love the tofu bacos, sweet potato fries and the vegetable egg rolls! I tried the tofu nacho-kim last week, it was satisfying and tastey. Service is great and the food is made to order, but they get you out fast.
Mexican + Asian = Amazin
Deliciosa! They have this fusion take of mexican and Asian pork dishes that are amazing!
got terrible food poisoning here. Would not recommend this place, or at least the duck soup.

The food is incredible and the staff is the friendliest I've ever encountered. Never thought I'd be considered a "regular" somewhere, but the folks at Spotted Monkey knew my name and order, and always greeted me with a smile.  My only complaint is that they aren't open on the weekends! I used to work downtown and could walk there any time I wanted to during lunch, but now that I work out of the city I never get to visit my favorite spot anymore!

Absolutely delicious. Gets really busy around lunch time - the line's almost out the door! But that's how you know this place is good. Most people get takeout but I stayed to eat at their high-top tables. Service was good, food even better. Quick and easy spot that I'll definitely go back to again!
Excellent service.  Food was not to my taste.  Not a fan of the pineapple on the tacos.  Everything was clean and people were nice.  I would go here again if they had different food!

Delicious option for lunch in the loop! I went late afternoon, didn't have to wait in line and easily found a table to sit at. I ordered the veggie egg rolls, shrimp baco & tofu baco. The veggie eggrolls were stellar! They come with a fantastic basil aioli that I literally smothered in everything. The shrimp baco, although a bit smaller than expected, was delicious. So much flavor and surprisingly filling. Lastly, the tofu baco (a vegan option), didn't carry as much flavor as I'd like. Maybe because it wasn't smothered in an amazing aioli like the other two? Who knows, but I wasn't a fan and probably won't order it again. Still had to give this place 5 stars, it was pretty great.

Saucy Porka will be included in my rotation. The flavors are great and portions are sufficient.  I've had their Asian paella several times. It's excellent,  carnitas and sliced sausage are the focus of the dish, and rice alone is very tasty. Also the curry sweet potato fries are recommended. They are a meal by themselves (if you like).  Looking forward to working through the rest of the menu.
Natalie is the best worker they have!
One of the best sandwich. I ordered short ribs and chorizo egg roll

The cashier ( i think her name is natalie?) Is super friendly and asked me  if I wanted any recommendations. I tried what she said and it was absolutely PHENOMENAL. I will be coming back and will be bringing all of my colleagues wish i could give her more stars.
Awesome food, awesome people. Recommend the Puerto Rican rice with pork and fried egg on top
Lunch gets pricey, but it's great.

Asian and Latin fusion? Yes, please! This was a great place to drop in for lunch or pick up lunch.  The service was fast and friendly.  Picadillo Eggroll $1.90 – Good, mostly filled with meat covered in a crunchy wrap. Puerto Rican yellow rice with pork ($11.50 with egg +$1.50) $13 – This dish was very good.  The rice was nice and chewy and the pork was tender.  I heard this place was from the same people that brought us Saucy Pork, so I knew to make sure I double check my food order before leaving.  Sure enough, one of two item was not found.  The key is to catch it before you leave.  The restaurant was easy to spot from the street with its bright yellow awning.

Pork baos and sweet potato fries are delicious! People working in there is very friendly and helpful. Very nice location. Price is very reasonable compared to restaurant around. I would definitely recommend it to anyone who are interested in an Asian bite.
Love the food here...chorizo egg rolls,rice bowls and bacos are great. friendly staff and good prices for loop area. Can be a little crowded during lunch...hope they expand soon.
Great sandwich with rich flavor.  Friendly and helpful staff.
Awesome unique food, everything looked so good.
Shh... Don't tell anyone how awesome the food and staff are... What this place for myself.
Decent food, but will not say that it is extraordinary or something we can't get elsewhere. But +1 for the service and friendly staff.
The ramen was very tasty and the small portion was perfect.
Go for the Asian Paella or one of the sandwiches. The baocos are pretty good but better as a side than trying to make a whole meal out of them.
spicy egg bahn mi for breakfast was delicious as were the beignets.
Yum! Trying to work my way through everything on the menu as it's all so good! The staff is super friendly here!
This is my favorite place in the Loop for lunch. Try the Asian Paella.
Went to the place on a friend's recommendation. Really liked it. Good food. Worth a try
Soooo 🔥

Super friendly, fast service, and the food was every bit as good as people said. I tried the tacos and egg rolls, both are great, unique combos of delicious ingredients. I didn't catch the name of the green dipping sauce I got, but that plus the sriracha was amazing. Will definitely remember this place on my next visit to Chicago.
Very tasty sandwiches with quick service at a reasonable price for the loop.
Delicious Latin-Asian fusion food--get the loaded fries, duck gumbo, or Puerto Rican rice with pork!
Great Food. Its definitely a taste bud friendly place with the Mix of the cultural foods.
Great food at a great price.   I had the chorizo egg rolls and sweet potato fries.   One of the best places I've been in the Chicago area.
Pretty good bacos. Expect a lunch wait.

Customer service was great, Food was seriously delicious. Had the loaded monkey fries, both types of egg rolls, ropa Viejo, pork taco,  and donuts. Our party of three left full and happy. Thanks for the recommendation Charisse.

This place is fantastic. The food is consistently executed and the staff is friendly. After trying a number of items on the menu including the bao tacos, sandwiches, and soups, I have yet to find anything I have not enjoyed. I highly recommend this restaurant.

So good! I met my boyfriend here for lunch on a rainy Friday morning at 11:30 and have been thinking about their duck gumbo fondly ever since. At 11:30 there was only 2 other people in the place, but as noon approached it quickly filled up. Employees put off a really good vibe and are friendly and welcoming. Pork bacos were also delicious!
Not bad.  Bao are small (can easily eat 5 of them).  No restroom in restaurant.  Eggroll was pretty good.  Excellent service and staff are very nice.
Great food. Be prepared for a line at lunch during the week.
Interesting fusion of Latin and Asian sandwiches. The staff there is also really nice and will make recommendations if you are new.

Amazing food and super fast service! I come here all the time on lunch to grab a few bacos (bao tacos) and I am never disappointed! Always good for a little snack or for a whole meal! Would absolutely recommend!
WOW! This place is an office favorite! You must go! order everything, but definitely order the duck baco! Your life will be changed.

Great food, great service. The food is an exceptional fusion of Latin and Asian, and it comes out super fast! The employees and very friendly and helpful too. Location is a little hard to find if you haven't been there before, but it's worth the search.

A fantastic gem in the Chicago financial district. This place serves Asian/Latin fusion and it does it incredibly well. Everything was fantastic from the friendly staff, fast food service and mouth watering apps and main dishes. The chorizo egg rolls are to die for and their Kim chi is top notch! If you are a fan of fusions then this is the place for you.

A very interesting combination of cuisines. Menu is not like anything I've experienced. Great place for an out of the ordinary lunch. Everything I tried was fantastic. Great place to eat lunch and staff was beyond helpful and friendly.
Great food and fast service. A bit pricey though.
You've got to try the picadilla egg rolls.
Best Asian fusion in the loop! Definitely get the pork bahn mi. It's like a flavor explosion!
Nice and different!
LOVE this restaurant. Nice people, great service, great authentic Italian food. Has a really nice small neighborhood bistro feel.
